body:
@ashwanthkumar I've been working on a version of this kind of feature where you could configure notification settings to pipelines via environment variables. The idea is to let global settings for all pipelines to be configured via plugin settings which then could be overridden with the pipeline environment variables. The variables would be `GO_SLACK_CHANNEL`, `GO_SLACK_STAGES` and `GO_SLACK_STATUSES`.

This change will require admin username and password to be configured for the plugin so that the plugin can get the pipeline configurations. Also it will require require GoCD version 15.3 or above which added the pipeline config API.

I have already implemented the basic plugin settings and the environment variable support. I still need to implement the global pipeline configurations and test it with my own GoCD pipelines.
